    "updated_at": "2025-02-28T09:12:38Z",
    "body": "One common approach to that is to support [`SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH`](https://reproducible-builds.org/docs/source-date-epoch/#rust) - in openSUSE, Debian and ArchLinux builds that is automatically set to the latest changelog entry.\nWould this need to go into the `shadow` crate?",
